{"name":"Faction Defender","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character is a well-known member of her faction and they’re more willing to help her out in time of need than most.<p>Favors (see page 34) cost one point less with members of the Ripper’s faction—to a minimum of one.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Persuasion d6, Status 3"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.PAFgtFYgIZIXUhK9"}},"_id":"mIkZ5B1UZyIinEkq"}
{"name":"Sound Mind","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This investigator has learned to cope with the terrors he must face and the dark things that lurk in his world. Increase his Sanity by +2.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fds2de065xm","path":"Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.yfmD2r0KworOzXnp"}},"_id":"pHkUesUV1J6d7Zgg"}
{"name":"Alternate Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your Ripper has another identity she can assume. The identity must be of lower Status than her own, and when assumed, incurs the relevant modifiers and station as usual.<p>People who know the individual in one identity and encounter the other make a Notice roll at –4, opposed by Stealth, to determine the truth. People who are more intimately familiar may suffer a reduced penalty, or none at all, at the Game Master’s discretion.<p>Scandals that affect the alter ego don’t affect the real individual. Also, since certain eccentricities are expected of such do-gooders, covering up Scandals (see page 34) costs one less Favor than usual.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Performance d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.SbI5rmok5lHU2YAe"}},"_id":"pyjpFRVY5KQurbeN"}
{"name":"Fortune Favors the Bold","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Explorers, cowboys, tomb raiders, and hired guns like Frazer’s Fighters fight creatures of darkness like all Rippers, but crave action and adventure (and sometimes treasure!) more than most other crusaders.<p>Fortune favors the bold, it is said, and those who go through secret initiations (similar to Masonic rituals) at their headquarters in Cairo are particularly blessed. The hero starts each session with one extra Benny (even if an Extra). This likely explains why so many of Frazer’s Fighters survive encounters and stunts others do not.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Frazer's Fighters)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.TVytAvupCS4kx5rr"}},"_id":"t3QwKV7HNFGVR2DH"}
{"name":"Sterner Stuff","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When this hero has rippertech implanted, the surgeon gains a +2 bonus to his Knowledge (Rippertech) roll due to the subject’s phenomenal constitution, raw willpower, or fierce determination.<p>In addition, the Ripper adds +2 to all Vigor rolls required when using extractions (including attempting to use multiple concoctions (see <b>Using Extracts,</b> page 47).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, V d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.H8XGEGTaDNfkvQ7Z"}},"_id":"tpsx8hDfrzmOWGew"}
{"name":"Down-to-Earth","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is of sound mind and not prone to flights of fancy. Although the supernatural is still frightening, he or she has the good sense to remain rooted in reality. A character with this Edge is more likely to be able to deal with the many horrors of the Cabal and can better resist rippertech’s harmful effects. Modify this hero’s Reason by +1.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.kARGTEGbUa8Uya9L"}},"_id":"wD2mZ6woGdDPEj4l"}
{"name":"Charms & Wards","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Witch hunters spend their days tracking down witches, hags, and rogue priests, and know how to prepare certain minor charms, tattoos, symbols, and even odors or ointments to ward off their evil eyes.<p>Black magic (and Special Abilities that mimic such power) used against the hero suffers a –2 penalty to the arcane skill roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Witch Hunter)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.lhBjTB5tYmPTmE1W"}},"_id":"yyurvt3FQ8Putzba"}
